<H1>Help about <I>Message</></H1>
</CENTER>
&nbsp;
</TD></TR><TR><TD>&nbsp;
<P>
<B><_ACRONYM_HTML_></B> provides a way to send messages to and receive messages
from other <B><_ACRONYM_HTML_></B> users directly without the use of e-mail.
<P>
To send a message, select the
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>Send =&gt; Message</B>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
menu item. In the window that appears, enter the <B><_ACRONYM_HTML_></B> user
id of the recipient in the <I<To</I> field and the body of the text
message in the large text area. Press the <B>Send</B> button, to transmit.
<P>
Within a few moments of the arrival of a message from another user,
the message icon (in the lower right of the main application screen
next to the stop sign) will become visible.  Either press the icon
or use the menu item
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>Show =&gt; Message</B>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
to retieve the message.
<P>
Until <B>Clear</B> is pressed, the messages will remain in your message
box.  It is a good idea to clear the messages when they are no longer needed.
<P></TD></TR><TR><TD BGCOLOR=#BBF1DE ALIGN=RIGHT>
